<p>Popular apps are often secretly sending personal data to marketing companies, or including invasive third-party trackers, or abusing permissions that they're granted, even in the background.</p>
<p>In our <strong>Privacy Reviews</strong> series, we dissect one app per review and tell you which third-party trackers it's using, what the trackers do, and what data they collect. We use the <a href="lockdownhq.com" target="_blank">Lockdown</a> app to automatically expose and block these behaviors.</p>

<p>For our first review, we chose the video chat app <strong>Houseparty</strong> due to its popularity, boosted by recent mandatory stay-at-home orders. Even though the app is free for its users, how much is the marketing data and tracking of 50+ million teens and young adults worth? We begin with a summary card, and delve into details below.
