  <h4 class="heading pb-1"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h4>
  
  <div class="row ml-4 mr-2 pb-3 bg-light rounded">
    <div class="col-md-9 text-left py-2 pt-4">
      <p>
      <strong>Houseparty gets a Privacy Grade of C+.</strong> While we can't certain exactly what Houseparty is sending to third parties, we know at the very least, every app activation and user action, along with unique identifiers are being sent for unknown processing. That totals to hundreds of data points per user (per day), multiplied by over 50 million users (and growing), multiplied by the number of different marketing and tracking companies involved.
      </p>
      <p>During our testing, we did not use Houseparty's "Connect To Facebook" feature. Had we done so, we would have likely logged Facebook Tracker blocking in addition to the other third parties above.
